				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In general: When you decode your maps, you'll have to decide which tile numbers are passable and which aren't.<br /><br />Specifically, SMB1 breaks metatiles into four groups depending on how they're colored in the attribute table: $00-$3F, $40-$7F, $80-$BF, and $C0-$FF. If I recall correctly, each group has a threshold: lower numbers are solid and higher numbers are passable.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

